<br>
Last evening while I was in Kelethin (as I had just achieved the 54th season) I heard shouts from none other than Galeth Veredeth. He had returned from Kunark with great news, that Fironia Vie had been rescued with the aid of her companions and was even as he spoke returning to the presence of her father King Tearis Thex.<br>
<br>
I approached and spoke with Galeth for a short time about the events that occurred and what the next move would be before Fironia expressed her wishes to move into the palace so she might see her father. A procession followed her into the city of Felwithe.<br>
<br>
While King Tearis Thex was pleased with Galeth for returning his daughter, he was angered that she had even been captured in the first place and stripped Lord Veredeth of his knighthood. I stood up for him, as I fought alongside him in the Battle of Bloody Kithicor, but my words were in vain and the King almost banished me for my disrespect. Fironia expressed her wish to meet with another friend of hers in the Lesser Faydark. Again we all set out...<br>
<br>
In the Lesser Faydark we walked only a short time before we came upon Equestrielle, the Unicorn of Tunare. Fironia expressed her wishes to summon the Avatar of Tunare to combat the evil forces that even now are encroaching Norrath. Equestrielle told us that this could be done with the help of the stones that were used to summon the other Avatars, and sent us back to Felwithe to enlist the aid of the King.<br>
<br>
Again in the presence of King Tearis Thex, Fironia told him of the Unicorn's instruction and the king immediately dispatched scouts to find the stones and bring to him his personal High Priest to perform the summoning. He then asked who had served her well during her travels of the past day. Neith, Lachinie, and myself were all awarded with coins of our particular virtue, to give to Lord Nethryn the Arbitrato in the inn in Felwithe. It is here that I received my ring, and was admitted into the Realm of Heroes.<br>
<br>
Notice the last part about Realm of Heroes.<br>
Saedyan Omniscient<br>
<br>
Fennin Ro<br>
